174 The funds appropriated for Workforce Development are to be expended for those costs
175 incurred by the State in honoring commitments to pay workforce development costs,
176 including services and other assistance and expenses of recruitment and training of
177 a company's workforce, that are undertaken to induce companies to locate and expand
178 their operations in Alabama (described hereinafter as a "Project") and to develop
179 and implement training, placement and recruitment programs that will improve
180 development and expand the State's workforce. Such costs include, but are not
181 limited to: (i) AIDT operating costs directly related to a Project; (ii) wages and
182 benefits for trainers engaged by AIDT for the purpose of a Project; (iii) costs
183 which the State has agreed to pay under the terms of a Project Agreement with a
184 company that are necessary and reasonable charges incurred by the company or its
185 affiliates for personnel providing training to the company's employees, whether
186 those trainers are employees of the company or its vendors or suppliers, including
187 wages, benefits and travel (domestic and, when necessary, international); (iv) any
188 necessary materials, equipment, manuals, or other relevant training materials; (v)
189 the costs incurred for purchasing or repairing or replacing training tools and
190 equipment; (vi) costs incurred for the purchase or construction and maintenance of
191 training facilities; (vii) travel expenses for prospective and current employees and
192 trainees, including travel, food, lodging, relocation, and other costs necessary and
193 reasonable to enable the company to secure a qualified workforce; and (viii) outside
194 training fees. The above funds appropriated for Workforce Development shall be
195 expended primarily for the training of Alabama residents. It is further the intent
196 that contracts with vendors to provide workforce training shall be inclusive and
197 reflect the racial and gender diversity of the State. The Secretary of the
198 Department of Commerce shall report semi-annually to the Chairs of the Senate
199 Committee on Finance and Taxation-Education, the House Ways and Means-Education
200 Committee, the Finance Director, and the Legislative Fiscal Officer any funds
201 allocated for workforce training. Such report shall include a summary of the persons
202 trained and the vendors providing the training. The report shall contain information
203 including the residence, race and gender of the persons trained and of the principal
204 or majority owner of the firm or business contracted with to provide the training
205 services.
