338 Scholarship Program
339 The Board of Trustees of the Alabama Community College System, in consultation
340 with the Alabama Industrial Development and Training Institute, shall
341 establish qualifications for the award of scholarships to high school students
342 and adults enrolled in a state educational program relating to the automotive
343 manufacturing industry and shall further provide for the implementation and
344 administration of the scholarships. Scholarship recipients shall be selected
345 by the Board, in consultation with a scholarship committee, comprised of
346 members of the Board of Directors of the Alabama Automotive Manufacturers
347 Association, from applications submitted to the association. The Board shall
348 file a report with the Chairs of the Senate Committee on Finance and
349 Taxation-Education, the House Ways and Means-Education Committee, the
350 Legislative Fiscal Officer, and the Finance Director on September 30, 2027
351 regarding the total number of scholarships awarded for the Fall term of the
352 2026-2027 academic year and the institution attended by the scholarship
353 recipients. The report shall also include the name of each scholarship
354 recipient and the number of years the recipient has received a scholarship.
