1002 The above appropriation includes funds to pay salary supplements and related benefit costs for
1003 Certified Academic Language Therapists (CALT) and other costs of the program. Supplement
1004 amounts will be determined by the availability of funds based on the number of CALT
1005 Teachers. The state of Alabama will provide an annual supplement of $5,000 to any CALT that is
1006 employed full-time in a public K-12 school system or public independent school and is properly
1007 certified by the state of Alabama. The existing eligibility criteria will apply: (a) CALTs
1008 employed on less than a full-time contract on October 1 will receive a pro-rata share of the
1009 salary supplement. (b) CALTs employed full-time after October 1 will receive a pro-rata share
1010 of the salary supplement. (c) Any CALT employed full-time in Alabama and properly certified by
1011 the state of Alabama will receive the annual salary stipend. (d) CALTs employed as a substitute
1012 are not eligible for the salary supplement. (e) CALTs who are on leave of absence for more than
1013 half a school year will receive a prorated amount based on the number of months worked during
1014 the school year. (f) CALTs will receive the salary supplement each year of the valid period of
1015 the CALT credentials unless the Alabama Legislature declines to make the annual appropriation.
1016 (g) CALTs must maintain their CALT credentials in order to continue receiving the salary
1017 supplement. (h) CALTs employed in the final year of their CALT credentials valid period will
1018 receive a prorated amount based on the number of months worked covered in that valid period.
1019 (i) CALTs who leave after October 1 will be eligible for a prorated amount based on the months
1020 served. (j) CALTs must remain employed with a public K-12 Local Board of Education school
1021 system or public independent school to continue receiving the salary supplement.
