1024 Of the above appropriation, $17,200,000 shall be expended for the Alabama Summer and
1025 Afterschool Program (ASAP) grants program with the objective of reducing the achievement gap in
1026 students who are not proficient in reading and/or math.
1027 The State Superintendent of Education shall administer the grants process. Grants shall be
1028 awarded to a) local education agencies, municipalities, and not-for-profit organizations for
1029 summer and afterschool programs that provide direct services and b) to entities that provide
1030 support to summer and after-school programs. Afterschool programs shall be guided by the
1031 Alabama Afterschool Quality Standards; summer programs shall be guided by the "Final Report and
1032 Recommendations" of the Alabama Campaign for Grade-Level Reading, Pages 81-92.
1033 Data on student and program outcomes shall be collected and used to inform a continuous
1034 improvement process. A report shall be provided to the Legislature listing grantees and
1035 summarizing outcomes.
1036 The intent of the Legislature is to increase access to evidence-based, high-quality summer and
1037 afterschool programming, to build a diverse delivery model of providers, and to foster
1038 collaboration between local education agencies and community-based organizations. The goal is
1039 to award at least 60% of the funding to nonprofit, community based organizations or
1040 partnerships between community-based organizations and local education agencies.
