1855 To be distributed as grants to monuments to commemorate historical events and places,
1856 historical skills centers, cultural heritage parks, historic sites, commissions, boards,
1857 agencies, and authorities that are not owned, operated, or otherwise under the control of the
1858 Alabama Historical Commission or other state agencies. Grants will be awarded to entities that
1859 reflect a historical education-based mission and concentrate on historical educational
1860 programming. Preference shall be given to: (1) any property constructed prior to 1840 that is
1861 listed in or eligible for the National Register of Historic Places and that are publicly owned
1862 and accessible to the public; or (2) any property in Alabama built in 1943 or before, and is
1863 listed in or eligible for the National Register of Historic Places or any property built after
1864 1943 that significantly contributed to the civil rights movement. The first three grants shall
1865 be reserved for Old State Bank for $200,000, Huntsville Historical Depot for $100,000, and Mt.
1866 Pinson Presbyterian Church for $75,000. Remaining grant amounts shall not exceed $100,000 for
1867 any one entity and must be used within two years of receiving the grant. Grants will not be
1868 awarded to any entity receiving funding directly or indirectly from the Education Trust Fund or
1869 the General Fund nor may grants be awarded to any private or for-profit business or
1870 organization.
