2805 (b) The above funds shall be utilized by the
2806 institutions to serve the needs of their student population in
2807 a manner that directly supports and advances the individual
2808 performance outcome categories selected by the Outcomes-Based
2809 Higher Education Funding Coordinating Committee in a manner to
2810 result in measurable improvements in the student success
2811 factors. Provided, however, bonus funding received by premier
2812 research universities for increased research expenditures may
2813 be used for enhancing and increasing research and innovation
2814 including equipment, instrumentation, and infrastructure
2815 (e.g., hardware and software); recruiting principal
2816 investigators, graduate research students; capital projects,
2817 including renovation of existing facilities; associated
2818 operating and maintenance costs; and matching funds for
2819 federal grants and contracts.
2820 Section 21. If any section, paragraph, sentence,
2821 clause, provision, or portion of this act or all or any
2822 portion of the appropriations herein made is held
2823 unconstitutional or invalid, it shall not affect any other
2824 section, paragraph, sentence, clause, provision, or portion of
